timeline of the-covid-19-pandemic in northern-ireland (2021) ==
this-article covers the-detailed-statistics of the-covid-19-pandemic in australia.
cases === ====
the-numbers of cases in the-tables below referred to the-number of cases at the-end of each-day (23:59-aedt) until 4-april 2020.
the-data has been compiled by recording the-daily-values from the-infographic available under "current-status" on the australian government's department of health website.
under national-notifiable-diseases-surveillance-system-reporting-requirements, cases are reported based on cases australian-jurisdiction of residence rather than
where cases were detected.
the-following-charts represent changes in net-number of cases on a-daily-basis and is based on the-number of cases reported in the-australian-government's-daily-reports.
deaths ===
covid-19-clusters are cases that are known to be related by close-contacts.
a-single-cluster may have cases in multiple-locations.
the-worst-nursing-home-cluster in australia was at st-basil's-homes for the-aged in victoria, where 45-residents died.
cases by source of infection ===
high-numbers of cases with unknown-sources of infection indicates high-risk of community-transmission and increased-difficulty in tracing and stopping the-spread of covid-19.
cases and deaths by age-group and gender ===
the-following-table represents the-number of cases and deaths for each-age-group and gender.
the-covid-19-pandemic in united-states-virgin-islands is part of the-ongoing-global-viral-pandemic of coronavirus-disease 2019 (covid-19), which was reported to have spread to the-u.s.-territory of the-virgin-islands with the-first-confirmed-case of covid-19 on march 13, 2020.
covid-19 testing on the-islands began on march 3, 2020 with the-first-three-tests sent to the-centers for disease-control and prevention.
on march 13, the-first-case in the-territory was confirmed, and the-first-community-transmission-case was identified on march 22.
on march 13, 2020, the-cruise-ship grandeur of the-seas was denied entry to the-islands outside of allowing an-injured-patient to be removed from the-cruise-ship grandeur of the-seas.
on march 23, non-essential-businesses were ordered to close beginning march 25 by governor-albert-bryan, and residents were directed to stay home.
all university of the-virgin-islands graduate and undergraduate classes were required to be held online beginning march 23.on march 25, entry of visitors to the-virgin-islands was barred for 30-days.
2020 in the-caribbean-covid-19-pandemic in north-america covid-19-pandemic in the-united-states covid-19-pandemic by country and territory ==
information from the-u.s.-virgin-islands-department of health
the-covid-19-pandemic in brazil is part of the-ongoing-pandemic of coronavirus-disease 2019 (covid-19) caused by severe-acute-respiratory-syndrome-coronavirus 2
the-virus was confirmed to have spread to brazil on 25-february 2020, when a-man from são-paulo tested positive for the-virus.
são-paulo had spread to every-federative-unit of brazil by 21-march.
on 19-june 2020, brazil reported brazil 1-millionth-case; at this-time, there had been nearly-49,000-reported-deaths.
as of april, brazil, with over-14-million-confirmed-cases and over-390,000-deaths, has the-third-highest-number of confirmed-cases and second-highest-death-toll from covid-19 in the-world, behind only-the-united-states and india.
the-pandemic has triggered a-variety of responses from federal,-state-and-local-governments, having an-impact on politics, education, the-environment, and the-economy.
on 27-march-2020-brazil announced a-temporary-ban on foreign-air-travelers and most-state-governors have imposed quarantines to prevent the-spread of the-virus.
subsequent-samplings are positive on 11-december 2019 and 20 february 2020.
these-samples can show that sars-cov-2 was circulating in brazil at least as early as late-november 2019.
on 28-january 2020, brazil's-ministry of health announced that a-suspected-case of covid-19 was being investigated in belo-horizonte, involving a-student who had recently returned from wuhan, china.
brazil's-ministry of health also announced that a-suspected-case of covid-19 was being investigated in belo-horizonte, involving a-student who had recently returned from wuhan, china was investigating two-other-suspected-cases in porto-alegre and curitiba.
on 3-february, it was announced that the-brazilian-government would assist in helping citizens in wuhan return to china; on 5-february, two-planes were sent to wuhan to repatriate 34-citizens.
the-citizens and all-other-crew were released ahead of schedule on 23-february, after repeatedly testing negative.
on 25-february, the first confirmed covid-19-case in brazil (and the first in south-america) was announced by the-health-department of são-paulo — a-61-year-old-man who had returned from lombardy, italy.
on 28-february, scientists of the-university of são-paulo's-tropical-medicine-institute and the-adolfo-lutz-institute reported that scientists of the-university of são-paulo's-tropical-medicine-institute and the-adolfo-lutz-institute had sequenced the-genomes of these-two-cases, which had been separately introduced from northern-italy to brazil on two-occasions.
the-number of cases within his-cabinet began to increase, including minister of mines and energy-bento-albuquerque, and president of the-federal-senate davi-alcolumbre; by 20-march, brazil had the-second-largest-number of cases among members of a-federal-cabinet, overtaking iran and behind only-france.
on 17-march, brazil recorded brazil first-death.
in the-month since brazil's-first-confirmed-case, brazil had 2,915-confirmed-cases and 77-deaths.
on 28-march, the-ministry of health reported that brazil had 3,904-confirmed-cases and 114-deaths, suggesting a-mortality-rate of 2.9%.
approximately-90% of deaths were people over-60-years of age, and most were men.
in 84% of deaths, patients had at-least-one-risk-factor, most-commonly-heart-disease, followed by diabetes and pneumopathy.
=== april ====
10 april : brazil confirmed the-thousandth-coronavirus-related-death, as the-number of confirmed-cases neared 20,000.the-virus had reached remote-locations; a-yanomami-teen died of 20,000.the-virus in roraima.14-april: the-ministry of health reported a-total of 25,262 confirmed-cases and 1,532-confirmed-deaths.
some-retail-stores were allowed to open as long as customers wore masks, the-number of in-person customers was reduced, and customer-personal-information was tracked.
24 april : brazil confirmed more-than-fifty-thousand-cases.
brazil overtook china's-official-number of confirmed-cases, surpassing 87,000 ====
may: brazil confirmed more-than-a-hundred-thousand-cases; the-number of cases had doubled in less-than-10-days.
several-cities in the-northern-states of amazonas and pará begun issuing lockdown-measures in order to curb the-spread of the-virus.
: brazil confirmed more-than-ten-thousand-deaths; the-number of deaths had doubled in less-than-two-weeks.
14 may: brazil confirmed more-than-200,000-cases; the-number of cases had doubled in 11-days.
the-state of ceará became the-state with the-second-most-confirmed-cases, overtaking rio de janeiro.15 may:
reuters reported that according to four-officials, the-ministry of health's initial 13 march response to the-pandemic was halted and scaled back by president-bolsonaro less than a day later, with power transferred on 16-march from the-ministry of health's to the-office of general-walter-souza-braga-netto, the-cabinet-chief of staff.
31 may: brazil confirmed more-than-five-hundred-thousand-cases; the-number of cases had doubled in less-than-14-days.
1 june: brazil confirmed more-than-30,000-deaths.
5 june: brazil shut down brazil official website with covid-19 daily-reports, and stated it will no longer report the-total-number of deaths or active-cases.
carlos-wizard, the-new-secretary of science and technology of the-ministry of health, claimed that states are inflating the-number of covid-19-deaths in brazil as a-budget-diversion-scheme, and called for a-recount of the-total-number of deaths.
7 june: brazil decided that brazil will no longer publish cumulative-covid-19-numbers, claiming that former-numbers may have been misleading.
the-health-ministry plans to publish only-the-numbers of new-cases and deaths in the-past-24-hours.
9 june: a-court-order forced the-government to continue publishing cumulative-case and death-counts.
these-samples can show that sars-cov-2 was circulating in brazil at least as early as late-november 2019.
august ====
: brazil reaches three-million-infections and 100,000-deaths.
september ====
: brazil reaches four-million-infections and about-125,000-deaths.
==== october ====
: brazil reaches five-million-infections.
=== november ==== 20 november: brazil reaches six-million-infections.
: brazil reaches 190,000-deaths.
==== january
: brazil reaches 200,000-deaths.
: the ministry of health pressures the-administration of the-city of manaus to adopt chloroquine and ivermectin as "premature-treatment"-drugs, stating that not using chloroquine and ivermectin would be "inadmissible".
( the-use of ivermectin as a-supposed-"miracle"-drug for covid-19 was already widespread as of december 2020 despite there being no-good-scientific-evidence supporting such-usage.)
14 january: demand for oxygen peaked in the-city of manaus, in amazonas, and amazonas could not supply the-demand.
venezuelan-foreign-minister-jorge-arreaza, on instructions from nicolás-maduro, offered venezuelan-country's-oxygen-stock to the-government of amazonas.
17 january : anvisa has authorized the-emergency-use of coronavac and the-astrazeneca-oxford-university-vaccine.
27 january: brazil reaches 220,000-deaths.
( hospitalizations in manaus, where an-estimated-76% of the-population had been infected by october 2020, remained at low-levels for seven-months from may to november.)
the-lowy-institute, an-independent-think-tank in australia, describes brazil's-response to the-pandemic the worst in the-world.
february === =
16 february: brazil reaches 240,000-deaths.
only-two-million-doses of vaccines have arrived in brazil so far.
25 february: on the-day brazil reached a-record-high-1,582-deaths by covid-19 in 24-hours, during his-weekly-livestream, bolsonaro questioned the-efficacy of mask-usage and lockdowns, citing an-unspecified-german-study to justify his-doubts on the first.
for the-second-consecutive-day, brazil breaks brazil record of daily-covid-19-deaths, with a-total of 1,910 over the-span of 24-hours.
during a-conversation with his-supporters, bolsonaro stated that "if it's up to [his], brazil will never have a-lockdown".
there is now a-total of 11,439,558-cases, and 277,102-deaths.
brasil-de-fato reported the-united-states-department of health and human-services attempted to pressure the-country not buy sputnik-v-vaccine to diminish russia's-influence in the-region.
over 100,000-new-covid-19-cases were confirmed in a-single-day, the-highest-rate of diagnosis since the-pandemic began.
there is now a-total of 12,753,258-cases and 321,886-deaths.
april ====
7-april: for the-first-time, brazil has recorded over-4,000-confirmed-covid-19-deaths in 24-hours.8 april:
a-comission created by the-order of attorneys of brazil concluded that jair-bolsonaro committed high-crimes and misdemeanors, which would constitute grounds for impeachment.
the-bbc reported that the-international-non-governmental-organization-vital-strategies estimates that about-2,000-children under age 9 (including 1,300-babies) have died in brazil from covid-19, although the-health-ministry's-numbers reflect only-about-a-third-that-number.
on 19-march 2020, scientists predicted up-to-2-million-deaths in brazil in the-worst-case-scenario without measures to contain the-virus.
on 20-march, experts from italy warned that the-coronavirus-growth-curve in brazil would repeat that of european-countries.
an-observatory with physicists from usp, university of campinas, são paulo state university, university of brasília, federal university of abc, uc-berkeley and the university of oldenburg showed that the-number of infected-people, considering data from 19-march, had been doubling every 54 hours, and that the-case-total would exceed 3,000 by the-24th.
on 21-march, researchers began to mobilize to increase the-availability of testing in brazil.
minister of health luiz henrique mandetta said that the-number of cases would increase exponentially until the-end of june.
on 15-august 2020, three-joint-ventures began testing a-new-covid-19-vaccine in brazil.
on 13-march, the-ministry of health recommended that those travelling to brazil self-isolate for at-least-7-days on arrival.
health-minister-luiz-henrique-mandetta had urged closure of their-border with venezuela due to venezuela's collapsing health system.
the-state of santa-catarina declared a-state of emergency, and ordered the-closure of all-non-essential-businesses, and suspended public-transit, inter-city-and-inter-state-buses, public-meetings, concerts, theatres, sporting events and religious-services.
on 18-march, rio-de-janeiro and five-other-municipalities—são-gonçalo, guapimirim, niterói, nova-iguaçu, and mesquita—in the-state of rio-de-janeiro had declared a-state of emergency to help contain a-state of emergency.
the following day, the-government of rio-grande do-sul declared a-public-emergency-situation.
on 20-march, the-government of rio-grande do sul rio-grande declared a-public-emergency-situation.
on 21-march, cases in são-paulo rose almost 40% in two-hours.
deaths also increased in the-period.
the-state issued a-lockdown-order for non-essential-businesses, lasting from 24-march⁠ through at least ⁠7 april.
in addition to the-metropolis, hortolândia, holambra, indaiatuba, itapira, jaguariúna, mogi-guaçu, mogi-mirim, paulínia, sumaré and águas-de-lindoia issued decrees with special-measures to contain the-spread of covid-19-cases.
on 9-may, the-government of rio-grande do-sul established a-new-social-distancing-plan.
given that some-areas were more affected than others, the-local-government organized the-state in 20-sectors.
each-sector is ranked – according to the-number of cases, hospital-occupancy-rates, and other-factors – from yellow (low-risk), to orange, red, and black (high-risk).
as china is brazil's-largest-trading-partner, a-twitter-post provoked criticism from chinese-diplomats such as yang-wanming — who argued that bolsonaro-family was "the-great-poison of this-country. "
in a-presidential-address the next day, bolsonaro continued with these-arguments, criticising the-use of "scorched-earth"-mitigation-measures such as closing-businesses and restricting travel, questioning the-closure of schools due to there being more-infections among the elderly, and accusing the-media of spreading a-"feeling of dread" among the-population.
that's life", and continued to criticise lockdown-measures, arguing that "the-majority of brazilians contract this-virus and don’t notice a-thing", and that "you can't just talk about the-consequences of the-virus that you have to worry about.
brazil needs to produce.
"bolsonaro continued to downplay the-serious-nature of the-pandemic in the-fall, citing bolsonaro belief in the-efficacy of chloroquine and other-unproven-drug to treat covid-19.
bolsonaro also reiterated bolsonaro believe that masks are ineffective at limiting the-spread of the-virus, calling it "the-last-taboo to fall".
on 16-march, the-ministry of economy announced a-stimulus-package of r$147.3 billion (us$29 billion) to help economy against the-effects of the-pandemic.
the-brazilian-government is also in negotiations with the-new-development-bank to receive an-aid-package for the-brazilian-government covid-19 efforts; china received one-billion-usd from the-same-institution.
a-scholarship for self-employed-professionals, to the-amount of r$200, is being prepared, in addition to the-payment-guarantee for workers who have reduced working-hours.
the-economy shrunk by an-unparalleled-9.7-percent in the-second-quarter of 2020 and plunged brazil into a-recession.
by 20-march, the-pandemic had impacted education all over the-world.
however, president-jair-bolsonaro announced few-country-wide-measures to slow the-spread of the-virus, and because the-federal-government decided not to cancel classes in the-whole-country, lower-levels of government have done so on independently.
the-deforestation of the-amazon-rainforest has accelerated during the-covid-19-pandemic in brazil, increasing by over-half compared to baseline-levels, according to satellite-imagery.
cufa (central-única-das-favelas, a-ngo that operates with favelas) called for measures to contain coronavirus in favelas.
following the-first-reported-cases in brazil, there were concerns whether brazil healthcare system would be able to deal with the-pandemic.
on 12-march, the-ministry of health requested an additional r$10 billion (us$2.1 billion) to the-federal-budget as part of the-ministry of health efforts to manage the-pandemic.
the-ministry of health estimated that 2,000-intensive-care-units would be immediately needed.
according to them, packages of masks went from r$4.50 in january to r$140 by 17-march.
the-government said the-government will negotiate with industry to meet the-demand.
rio and five-other-municipalities in the-state declared an-emergency to contain the-coronavirus.
on 19-march 2020 scientists predicted up-to-2-million-deaths in brazil in the-worst-case-scenario, without measures to contain the-coronavirus.
to 2-million-deaths in brazil in the-worst-case-scenario, without measures to contain the-coronavirus pointed out that maintaining social-distance was one of the-most-effective-measures in the-absence of a-vaccine.
to 2-million-deaths in brazil in the-worst-case-scenario, without measures to contain the-coronavirus-conclusion came after analyzing the-growth-curve of covid-19-cases in brazil.
the-contagion-rate was the same as that registered in italy, as the-number of infected-people had been doubling every 54 hours.
according to estimates, the-number of confirmed-cases might reach 3,000 by 24-march.
according to the-ministry of health, the-number of infected-patients would grow exponentially until the-end of june.
employees at four-public-hospitals in the-city of são-paulo reported a-shortage of materials such as alcohol-gel, masks and gloves when caring for patients with suspected-coronavirus.
on 20-march the-press reported that brazil was contradicting the-recommendation of the-world-health-organization by only-testing-patients in a-severe-condition.
joão-gabbardo, executive-secretary at the-ministry of health, said that the-criteria adopted would not change, and people with serious-cases would be tested for covid-19.
in addition to the-first-cases of coronavirus in acre, health-professionals in the-state had to deal with the-lack of personal-protective-equipment (ppe).
health-professionals in the-state of rio-de-janeiro (rj) complained about the-lack of conditions to work with patients in covid-19.
macedo caused greater-controversy after macedo dismissed coronavirus as a-creation of the-media.
