the-betacoronaviruses of the-greatest-clinical-importance concerning humans are oc43 and hku1 (which can cause the-common-cold) of lineage-a, sars-cov and sars-cov-2 (which causes the-disease covid-19) of lineage-b, and mers-cov of lineage-c. mers-cov is the-first-betacoronavirus belonging to lineage-c that is known to infect humans.
this-morphology is created by the-viral-spike-(s)-peplomers, which are proteins that populate the-surface of the-virus and determine host-tropism.
contributing to genetic-diversity in the-african-camel-population are several--recombination-events that had taken place in the-past between closely-related-betacoronaviruses of the-subgenus-embecovirus.
