scotland were developing surveillance was shortly to be extended to some-hospitals and gp-surgeries in scotland
on 21-march, welsh-government-health-minister-vaughan-gething said that the-target was 9,000-tests by the-end of april.
public-health-england said that public-health-england had not interfered with any-contract but said "welsh-government-health recently asked us to establish a-partnership with roche to support increased-diagnostic-testing in the-uk for covid-19."on 21
the-welsh-government announced that one of the-new-antibody-blood-tests for the-sars-cov-2-virus is being produced by ortho-clinical-diagnostics (ocd) at pencoed, wales, in partnership with public health wales.
uk-research and innovation will deliver large-scale,-rapid-whole-genome-sequencing of the-virus that causes the-disease and £260 million to the-coalition for epidemic preparedness innovations to support vaccine-development.
